   "source": [
    "The watershed workflow transformed the DEM into a hydrologically connected surface, then modeled flow, extracted streams, snapped a pour point to the drainage network, and delineated a watershed polygon. The final accumulation and stream patterns should align with valleys and mapped hydrography, suggesting the routing results are reasonable.\n",
    "\n",
    "The LiDAR workflow inspected and cleaned the point cloud, then generated DSM, DEM, and CHM rasters. Together, these outputs separate bare earth from above-ground features and make it possible to interpret surface height, vegetation, and built form."
   ]
